<p>President Trump announced he would designate Nigeria a &quot;country of particular concern&quot; for religious freedom, saying Christianity in Nigeria faces an &quot;existential threat,&quot; and ordering the addition on Friday while posting about it on his Truth Social account . The move formally puts Nigeria on a State Department watch list that can trigger diplomatic pressure and possible punitive measures, and it follows calls from some U.S. lawmakers for action . Experts and analysts have disputed claims of a targeted &quot;Christian genocide,&quot; saying violence in Nigeria is driven by multiple armed groups and has killed and displaced people of different faiths over many years .</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/4hfEr0d-Z9gQxSxexV9QRAmY-s9S6z0fLY2hHoQqzP4SATa9CaxLgLJy0sHCegoVHCH7OLzpHFJOkGFwDUFWATF-iC8fr4aB4aG9mw42BoYKIuuTJI4uTMwbWkhcaJXnQTEXrN1wRbuONIGjUnqseziMU7sNepNUVm5WcL9DFbnWDhAlX1d-n_oUSnWalBwtCpxjP_A' alt='File image used in coverage of U.S. reaction to violence in Nigeria' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Sanctions mechanism: A &quot;country of particular concern&quot; designation allows the U.S. to pursue measures such as restrictions on assistance or other penalties, effectively opening the door to sanctions against Nigeria</li><li>Congressional push: President Trump publicly urged the House Appropriations Committee to investigate the killings in Nigeria and provide a report to Congress, a request amplified on his Truth Social account</li><li>Long-term violence: Boko Haram&#x27;s insurgency and related conflicts have killed tens of thousands and forced millions from their homes over the last decade and a half, complicating claims that violence is only against Christians</li><li>Narrative spread: Claims of mass persecution of Christians in Nigeria have circulated widely on social media and gained traction among some American and European far-right actors, according to analysts cited in reporting</li></ul><blockquote>Christianity is facing an existential threat in Nigeria. - President Donald Trump</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>President Trump / White House: Mr. Trump said thousands of Christians are being killed and named Nigeria a country of particular concern over religious freedom, framing the designation as a response to what he called an existential threat to Christianity . (<a href='https://www.cbsnews.com/news/trump-says-christians-face-existential-threat-in-nigeria/'>CBS News</a>)</li><li>Human rights experts and analysts: Scholars and analysts warned that violence in Nigeria is complex, driven by jihadist groups, criminal bandits and communal clashes that have harmed both Christians and Muslims, disputing claims of a one-sided campaign of mass murder . (<a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2025/10/31/trump-places-nigeria-on-watch-list-over-claims-of-anti-christian-violence'>Al Jazeera</a>)</li><li>U.S. right-wing lawmakers: Some Republican lawmakers, including Senator Ted Cruz and other allies, pressed for stronger action and have publicly pushed narratives describing mass killings of Christians in Nigeria . (<a href='https://www.allsides.com/news/2025-10-31-0700/religion-and-faith-trump-calls-congress-investigate-nigeria-radical-islamists-massacre-thousands-christians'>AllSides</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2025/10/31/trump-places-nigeria-on-watch-list-over-claims-of-anti-christian-violence'>Trump places Nigeria on watch list over claims of anti-Christian violence</a> - aljazeera.com</li><li><a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/trump-says-christians-face-existential-threat-in-nigeria-adds-country-to-watch-list'>Trump says Christians face ‘existential threat’ in Nigeria, adds country to watch list</a> - straitstimes.com</li><li><a href='https://www.cbsnews.com/news/trump-says-christians-face-existential-threat-in-nigeria/'>Trump says Christians face threats in Nigeria, opens door for sanctions</a> - cbsnews.com</li><li>